caption: The image illustrates a bar magnet oriented at an angle θ within a uniform magnetic field represented by horizontal dashed arrows labeled 'B'. The north pole (N) and south pole (S) of the magnet are clearly marked, with the magnet's axis forming an angle with the direction of the magnetic field. This setup is commonly used to explain the torque experienced by a magnetic dipole in an external magnetic field.
key_elements: Bar magnet with poles labeled N and S
Angle θ between the magnet's axis and the magnetic field
Torque effect on a magnetic dipole
scientific_context: This diagram is relevant in electromagnetism, specifically in the study of magnetic dipoles and their interaction with external magnetic fields. It helps in understanding the principles behind the behavior of magnets in various applications, such as electric motors and generators.
